\paragraph{Context}
The definition concerns $G$-stability for one-leg methods applied to nonlinear ODEs. The matrix $M$ arises from an identity comparing differences between numerical solutions $y_n$ and $z_n$, and its positive semi-definiteness ensures stability.

Variables:
\begin{itemize}
    \item $M$: matrix defined by equation (451e)
    \item $[\alpha, \beta]$: one-leg method defined by generating polynomials $\alpha(z)$ and $\beta(z)$
    \item $G$: positive definite matrix used in the norm $\|\cdot\|_G$
\end{itemize}

Referenced equations:
\begin{equation}
    M = [m_{ij}], \quad \text{where } m_{ij} \text{ are coefficients from the identity involving } G, \alpha_i, \beta_i
    \tag{451e}
\end{equation}
